üî∑ Result

The program successfully cracked the ZIP file password using a dictionary wordlist.



üî∂ PART B: Brute-force vs Dictionary Attack on SHA-1 Hashed Password

üî∑ Algorithm (SHA-1 Cracking):

	Brute-force: Try all combinations of letters up to a certain length.



	Dictionary: Try all words from a wordlist file.



üî∑ Python Program ‚Äì Brute Force



import hashlib

import itertools

import string



target_hash = hashlib.sha1(b'abc123').hexdigest()



for length in range(1, 6):

    for attempt in itertools.product(string.ascii_lowercase + string.digits, repeat=length):

        guess = ''.join(attempt)

        hashed = hashlib.sha1(guess.encode()).hexdigest()

        if hashed == target_hash:

            print("‚úÖ Password cracked:", guess)

            exit()



üî∑ Python Program ‚Äì Dictionary Attack



import hashlib



target_hash = hashlib.sha1(b'abc123').hexdigest()



with open('wordlist.txt', 'r') as f:

    for word in f:

        guess = word.strip()

        if hashlib.sha1(guess.encode()).hexdigest() == target_hash:

            print("‚úÖ Password cracked using dictionary:", guess)

            break



üî∑ Output (Example)



‚úÖ Password cracked using dictionary: abc123
